**[1848, 11-12] Ms.A.1.2.18.39**

EPN to WLG; Edinburgh.

Hopes that “hydropathy may do as much for thee as under the blessing of
God, it has done for me.” Elihu Burritt is optimistic about the results
of the Brussels congress, and while it is good to rejoice in “every
movement in the right direction,” she cannot feel the same enthusiasm
for EB that generally prevails because his efforts “do not seem to me to
be directed to the root of the evil. So also with the Free Labour
movement in this country & as to the free soil movement in yours I
cannot understand how any true Anti Slavery person can join it.”


